The program is correct, it should print out 20 which corresponds to the "ta
"target" record in the given list. Here's the Tundra source code for refere
reference:

```tundra
val rows = [
  { label: "low", value: 10 },
  { label: "target", value: 20 },
  { label: "high", value: 30 }
];

val selected = rows[1]; //Changed from 2 to 1, as the index in Tundra start
starts at 0.
print(selected.value);
```
